WEBVTT

1
00:00:12.587 --> 00:00:15.439
To be honest, by personality,
说实话，从性格上来讲，

2
00:00:15.439 --> 00:00:18.056
I'm just not much of a crier.
我并不是一个容易流泪的人。

3
00:00:19.136 --> 00:00:22.416
But I think in my career that's been a good thing.
但考虑到我的职业， 能有这个性格是件好事。

4
00:00:23.066 --> 00:00:24.450
I'm a civil rights lawyer,
我是一名民权律师，

5
00:00:24.450 --> 00:00:27.454
and I've seen some  horrible things in the world.
我见过一些发生在 全球各地的可怕的事情。

6
00:00:28.854 --> 00:00:32.664
I began my career working  police abuse cases in the United States.
我的第一份职业是在美国 处理警察滥用职权的案子。

7
00:00:32.664 --> 00:00:36.138
And then in 1994, I was sent to Rwanda
后来，1994年，我被派往卢旺达，

8
00:00:36.138 --> 00:00:41.068
to be the director of the U.N.'s  genocide investigation.
领导联合国种族灭绝调查组。

9
00:00:41.728 --> 00:00:45.467
It turns out that tears  just aren't much help
我发现，当你调查 种族灭绝的惨案时，

10
00:00:45.467 --> 00:00:48.996
when you're trying  to investigate a genocide.
泪水派不上多大用场。

11
00:00:48.996 --> 00:00:53.857
The things I had to see,  and feel and touch
那些我不得不面对的事实， 那些令我感触深刻的故事，

12
00:00:53.857 --> 00:00:56.684
were pretty unspeakable.
都难以名状。

13
00:00:57.354 --> 00:01:00.711
What I can tell you is this:
我可以明确告诉你们的是：

14
00:01:00.711 --> 00:01:02.808
that the Rwandan genocide
卢旺达种族灭绝是

15
00:01:02.808 --> 00:01:08.481
was one of the world's greatest failures of simple compassion.
缺乏同情导致的 全世界最惨的惨案之一。

16
00:01:09.531 --> 00:01:12.940
That word, compassion, actually  comes from two Latin words:
"同情"这个词 来源于两个拉丁词汇：

17
00:01:12.940 --> 00:01:18.462
cum passio, which simply mean  "to suffer with."
cum和passio， 其含义是"同甘苦"。

18
00:01:18.462 --> 00:01:22.024
And the things that I saw and experienced
目睹卢旺达的惨案，

19
00:01:22.024 --> 00:01:24.610
in Rwanda as I got up close to human suffering,
我感受到了那里的 人们所承受的苦难，

20
00:01:24.610 --> 00:01:27.949
it did, in moments, move me to tears.
这让我落下泪水。

21
00:01:27.949 --> 00:01:30.675
But I just wish that I,  and the rest of the world,
我多么希望， 我，以及整个世界，

22
00:01:30.675 --> 00:01:33.190
had been moved earlier.
可以在一切发生前就投以同情。

23
00:01:33.190 --> 00:01:34.854
And not just to tears,
不单单是落下同情的泪水，

24
00:01:34.854 --> 00:01:38.654
but to actually stop the genocide.
更要切实阻止这场惨案。

25
00:01:38.654 --> 00:01:41.112
Now by contrast, I've also been involved
与之对比，我也经历了

26
00:01:41.112 --> 00:01:46.945
with one of the world's greatest successes of compassion.
同情带来的最美好的硕果之一。

27
00:01:46.945 --> 00:01:49.891
And that's the fight against  global poverty.
这就是全世界范围内 拯救贫困的运动。

28
00:01:49.891 --> 00:01:52.674
It's a cause that probably has involved all of us here.
这场运动或许 跟在座的每个人都相关。

29
00:01:52.674 --> 00:01:54.672
I don't know if your first introduction
我不知道是什么让 你们初次了解到世界贫困问题，

30
00:01:54.672 --> 00:01:58.037
might have been choruses of "We Are the World,"
是"天下一家"这一合唱曲，

31
00:01:58.037 --> 00:02:02.100
or maybe the picture of a sponsored child on your refrigerator door,
还是你们家冰箱门上贴着的 受到救济的儿童的照片，

32
00:02:02.100 --> 00:02:06.187
or maybe the birthday you donated for fresh water.
还是你把过生日的钱拿去 捐给了水质净化项目？

33
00:02:06.187 --> 00:02:09.401
I don't really remember what my first introduction to poverty was
我不记得是什么让我 第一次了解到贫困问题，

34
00:02:09.401 --> 00:02:12.965
but I do remember the most jarring.
但我记得给我留下 最深刻印象的一次经历，

35
00:02:12.965 --> 00:02:15.127
It was when I met Venus --
那一次我见到了Venus，

36
00:02:15.127 --> 00:02:17.849
she's a mom from Zambia.
她是来自赞比亚的一位母亲，

37
00:02:17.849 --> 00:02:21.475
She's got three kids and she's a widow.
她是一个遗孀，有三个孩子。

38
00:02:21.475 --> 00:02:24.842
When I met her, she had walked about 12 miles
她走了大概12英里 才到了我们碰面的地方，

39
00:02:24.842 --> 00:02:27.515
in the only garments she owned,
她穿着唯一的一套衣服，

40
00:02:27.515 --> 00:02:31.777
to come to the capital city and to share her story.
来到首都，向我讲述她的故事。

41
00:02:31.777 --> 00:02:35.392
She sat down with me for hours,
她坐着跟我聊了好几个小时，

42
00:02:35.392 --> 00:02:39.917
just ushered me in to  the world of poverty.
让我深刻体会到了 贫穷世界究竟是何等模样。

43
00:02:39.917 --> 00:02:43.058
She described what it was like  when the coals on the cooking fire
她向我描述着一幅幅贫困的画面：

44
00:02:43.058 --> 00:02:46.787
finally just went completely cold.
煮食炉火的煤烧尽、凉透，

45
00:02:46.787 --> 00:02:51.549
When that last drop  of cooking oil finally ran out.
最后一滴食用油消耗殆尽，

46
00:02:51.549 --> 00:02:55.405
When the last of the food,  despite her best efforts,
尽管她极力节衣缩食，依然耗尽了

47
00:02:55.405 --> 00:02:56.513
ran out.
最后一口食物。

48
00:02:57.933 --> 00:03:00.916
She had to watch her youngest son, Peter,
她不得不眼睁睁地 看着小儿子 Peter

49
00:03:00.916 --> 00:03:03.698
suffer from malnutrition,
遭受营养不良的折磨，

50
00:03:03.698 --> 00:03:07.774
as his legs just slowly bowed  into uselessness.
他的双腿渐渐萎缩， 丧失了行走的能力。

51
00:03:07.774 --> 00:03:11.122
As his eyes grew cloudy and dim.
他的眼睛变得黯淡无光，

52
00:03:11.122 --> 00:03:15.300
And then as Peter finally grew cold.
直到最后，他的身子变冰冷了。

53
00:03:17.950 --> 00:03:23.631
For over 50 years, stories like this have been moving us to compassion.
过去的五十多年间， 这样的故事激起了我们的同情心，

54
00:03:23.631 --> 00:03:26.481
We whose kids have plenty to eat.
同情那些吃不饱饭的孩子。

55
00:03:26.481 --> 00:03:29.150
And we're moved not only  to care about global poverty,
我们不只是在心里 默默关心全球贫困问题，

56
00:03:29.150 --> 00:03:33.840
but to actually try to do our part  to stop the suffering.
还尽了自己的一份力， 让贫困的人不再受苦受难。

57
00:03:33.840 --> 00:03:37.313
Now there's plenty of room for critique  that we haven't done enough,
有很多方面我们做的还不够，

58
00:03:37.313 --> 00:03:41.535
and what it is that we've done hasn't been effective enough,
我们做的很多事情效果还不够显著，

59
00:03:41.535 --> 00:03:44.665
but the truth is this:
但事实是：

60
00:03:44.665 --> 00:03:48.216
The fight against global poverty is probably the broadest,
抗击世界贫困的运动很可能是

61
00:03:47.706 --> 00:03:53.351
longest running manifestation of the  human phenomenon of compassion
人类出于同情心而发起的 有史以来涉及范围最广，

62
00:03:53.351 --> 00:03:56.493
in the history of our species.
持续时间最为长久的运动。

63
00:03:56.493 --> 00:04:00.142
And so I'd like to share a pretty shattering insight
我会给你们分享一些我的见解，

64
00:04:00.142 --> 00:04:04.435
that might forever change the way you think about that struggle.
或许会永远改变大家 对这场运动的认识。

65
00:04:04.435 --> 00:04:07.258
But first, let me begin with what you probably already know.
但首先，我来谈一下你们大多 已经知道的一些事实。

66
00:04:07.258 --> 00:04:10.740
Thirty-five years ago, when I would have been graduating from high school,
35年前，我快要从高中毕业的时候，

67
00:04:10.740 --> 00:04:17.117
they told us that 40,000 kids every day died because of poverty.
有数据表明每天有 四万个儿童死于饥饿。

68
00:04:17.117 --> 00:04:21.489
That number, today, is now  down to 17,000.
今天，这个数字下降到一万七千。

69
00:04:21.489 --> 00:04:23.495
Way too many, of course,
当然，还是很多，

70
00:04:23.495 --> 00:04:26.172
but it does mean that every year,
但这确实表明，

71
00:04:24.982 --> 00:04:31.490
there's eight million kids who don't have to die from poverty.
每年都有八百万名儿童 不会因饥饿而离开这个世界。

72
00:04:31.470 --> 00:04:33.887
Moreover, the number of  people in our world
而且，全世界生活在

73
00:04:33.887 --> 00:04:36.050
who are living in extreme poverty,
极度贫困状态的人数

74
00:04:36.050 --> 00:04:39.387
which is defined as living off about a dollar and a quarter a day,
——极度贫困的定义是 每天用于糊口的钱不超过1.25美金——

75
00:04:39.387 --> 00:04:42.999
that has fallen from 50 percent,
已经从世界人口的50%

76
00:04:42.999 --> 00:04:46.233
to only 15 percent.
下降到只有15%。

77
00:04:47.223 --> 00:04:48.673
This is massive progress,
这是卓越的进步，

78
00:04:48.673 --> 00:04:53.498
and this exceeds everybody's  expectations about what is possible.
超出了所有人的预期。

79
00:04:54.078 --> 00:04:56.943
And I think you and I,
我认为我们所有人，

80
00:04:56.943 --> 00:05:01.219
I think, honestly, that we can  feel proud and encouraged
说实话， 我们应当为此而感到自豪，

81
00:05:01.219 --> 00:05:05.104
to see the way that compassion  actually has the power
能够见证同情迸发出的力量

82
00:05:05.104 --> 00:05:10.296
to succeed in stopping  the suffering of millions.
如何解救了数以百万计的人们。

83
00:05:10.296 --> 00:05:14.672
But here's the part that you  might not hear very much about.
但后面这个数据 你们可能没听说过。

84
00:05:14.672 --> 00:05:19.406
If you move that poverty mark just up to two dollars a day,
如果把贫困线稍稍上移， 设为一天2美金，

85
00:05:19.406 --> 00:05:22.405
it turns out that virtually  the same two billion people
你就会发现世界上仍然有20亿人

86
00:05:22.405 --> 00:05:26.217
who were stuck in that harsh poverty when I was in high school,
生活在极度贫困的状态下，

87
00:05:26.217 --> 00:05:28.098
are still stuck there,
我上高中时有这么多人，

88
00:05:28.098 --> 00:05:30.487
35 years later.
35年后的今天依然是。

89
00:05:30.487 --> 00:05:35.506
So why, why are so many billions still stuck in such harsh poverty?
为什么呢？为什么有好几十亿人 深陷贫困的深渊？

90
00:05:36.216 --> 00:05:39.171
Well, let's think about Venus for a moment.
让我们再回到Venus的故事。

91
00:05:39.171 --> 00:05:42.943
Now for decades, my wife and I have been moved by common compassion
数十年来，我的夫人和我出于同情

92
00:05:42.943 --> 00:05:45.772
to sponsor kids, to fund microloans,
帮助孩子，资助小额贷款，

93
00:05:45.772 --> 00:05:49.291
to support generous levels of foreign aid.
慷慨地支持国外援救行动。

94
00:05:49.291 --> 00:05:52.383
But until I had actually talked to Venus,
但直到我亲身跟Venus攀谈后，

95
00:05:52.383 --> 00:05:55.020
I would have had no idea that  none of those approaches
我才知道以前所做的一切 都没有切中要害，

96
00:05:55.020 --> 00:06:00.516
actually addressed why she had to watch her son die.
以致于她不得不眼睁睁地 看着她的孩子死去。

97
00:06:01.626 --> 00:06:06.063
"We were doing fine," Venus told me,
“本来我们过得挺好，” Venus告诉我，

98
00:06:06.063 --> 00:06:10.605
"until Brutus started to cause trouble."
”直到Brutus开始惹麻烦。“

99
00:06:10.605 --> 00:06:13.575
Now, Brutus is Venus' neighbor  and "cause trouble"
Brutus是Venus的邻居， ”惹麻烦“是指

100
00:06:13.575 --> 00:06:17.101
is what happened the day after Venus' husband died,
Venus丈夫去世后的第二天，

101
00:06:17.101 --> 00:06:21.033
when Brutus just came and threw Venus and the kids out of the house,
Brutus将Venus 和她的孩子们赶出了家门，

102
00:06:21.033 --> 00:06:24.785
stole all their land, and robbed their market stall.
掠去了所有的土地， 抢走了值钱的东西。

103
00:06:26.205 --> 00:06:31.162
You see, Venus was thrown  into destitution by violence.
是暴力让Venus陷入贫困。

104
00:06:32.702 --> 00:06:34.711
And then it occurred to me, of course,
这让我突然间意识到，

105
00:06:34.711 --> 00:06:38.510
that none of my child sponsorships, none of the microloans,
我的儿童资助、小额贷款、

106
00:06:38.510 --> 00:06:42.372
none of the traditional  anti-poverty programs
传统的抗击贫困的运动，

107
00:06:42.372 --> 00:06:46.338
were going to stop Brutus,
都无法阻止Brutus，

108
00:06:46.338 --> 00:06:49.692
because they weren't meant to.
因为所做的一切都没切中要害。

109
00:06:49.692 --> 00:06:54.698
This became even more clear to me when I met Griselda.
当我遇到Griselda后， 我更加清晰地意识到这个问题。

110
00:06:54.698 --> 00:06:58.917
She's a marvelous young girl living in a very poor community
她是一个美丽的年轻女子，

111
00:06:57.207 --> 00:07:00.733
in Guatemala.
住在危地马拉 一个贫困不堪的社区。

112
00:07:00.733 --> 00:07:03.130
And one of the things we've learned over the years
根据我们过去的经验，

113
00:07:03.130 --> 00:07:05.701
is that perhaps the most powerful thing
我们认为让Griselda和她的家庭

114
00:07:05.701 --> 00:07:08.545
that Griselda and her family can do
走出贫困的最有效的办法，

115
00:07:08.545 --> 00:07:11.210
to get Griselda and her family  out of poverty
或许就是确保

116
00:07:11.210 --> 00:07:14.334
is to make sure that she goes to school.
Griselda能够完成学业。

117
00:07:14.334 --> 00:07:19.059
The experts call this the Girl Effect.
专家称之为“女孩效应”。

118
00:07:19.059 --> 00:07:23.141
But when we met Griselda,  she wasn't going to school.
但当我们遇到Griselda时， 她并没有上学。

119
00:07:23.141 --> 00:07:26.698
In fact, she was rarely ever  leaving her home.
事实上，她几乎走不出家门。

120
00:07:28.208 --> 00:07:29.993
Days before we met her,
在我们遇见她的几天前，

121
00:07:29.993 --> 00:07:32.638
while she was walking home from church with her family,
当她离开教堂， 跟家人走在回家的路上时，

122
00:07:32.638 --> 00:07:34.953
in broad daylight,
光天化日之下，

123
00:07:34.953 --> 00:07:38.430
men from her community  just snatched her off the street,
她所在社区的几个男人 把她从街道上拉走，

124
00:07:38.430 --> 00:07:41.528
and violently raped her.
强暴了她。

125
00:07:41.528 --> 00:07:46.025
See, Griselda had every opportunity to go to school,
所以，Griselda并不缺少上学的机会，

126
00:07:46.025 --> 00:07:49.446
it just wasn't safe for her to get there.
只是上学的路上太不安全了。

127
00:07:49.446 --> 00:07:52.286
And Griselda's not the only one.
Griselda并不是唯一 面临这个问题的孩子。

128
00:07:52.286 --> 00:07:55.010
Around the world, poor women and girls
全世界，在15到44岁之间的

129
00:07:55.010 --> 00:08:00.121
between the ages of 15 and 44,
贫困的妇女和女孩中，

130
00:08:00.121 --> 00:08:04.206
they are -- when victims of  the everyday violence
因日常家庭暴力和性暴力侵犯

131
00:08:04.206 --> 00:08:07.692
of domestic abuse and sexual violence --
而丧生或残疾的人数

132
00:08:07.692 --> 00:08:12.504
those two forms of violence account for more death and disability
要超过因疟疾、交通事故、战争

133
00:08:12.504 --> 00:08:19.508
than malaria, than car accidents, than war combined.
而死亡或残疾的妇女数量之和。

134
00:08:23.118 --> 00:08:27.895
The truth is, the poor of our world are trapped in whole systems of violence.
真相是，全世界的穷人 都深陷暴力的牢笼。

135
00:08:27.895 --> 00:08:31.928
In South Asia, for instance, I could drive past this rice mill
比如说，在南亚， 我开车驶过一片稻田，

136
00:08:31.928 --> 00:08:34.865
and see this man hoisting  these 100-pound sacks
看到这个男人用他瘦弱的后背

137
00:08:34.865 --> 00:08:36.909
of rice upon his thin back.
驼着100磅重的米袋。

138
00:08:36.909 --> 00:08:38.727
But I would have no idea, until later,
但当时我根本就没想到，

139
00:08:38.727 --> 00:08:41.169
that he was actually a slave,
他原来是一个奴隶，

140
00:08:41.169 --> 00:08:45.558
held by violence in that rice mill since I was in high school.
在我上着高中时， 他就被迫碾米作坊劳作。

141
00:08:46.648 --> 00:08:50.059
Decades of anti-poverty programs right in his community
数十年来，他所在社区的 抗击贫困的运动

142
00:08:50.059 --> 00:08:54.141
were never able to rescue him or any of the hundred other slaves
都没能解救他， 也没能解救作坊中其他

143
00:08:54.141 --> 00:08:57.777
from the beatings and the rapes and the torture
遭受殴打、强暴、酷刑的

144
00:08:57.777 --> 00:09:01.472
of violence inside the rice mill.
百余名奴隶。

145
00:09:01.472 --> 00:09:05.852
In fact, half a century of  anti-poverty programs
事实上，相对于 人类历史上其他任何时刻，

146
00:09:05.852 --> 00:09:09.526
have left more poor people in slavery
近半世纪以来的抗击贫困的运动，

147
00:09:09.526 --> 00:09:12.891
than in any other time in human history.
让人类历史上沦为奴隶的人数达到了顶峰。

148
00:09:12.891 --> 00:09:18.870
Experts tell us that there's about 35 million people in slavery today.
专家告诉我们， 世界上目前大概有三千五百万奴隶。

149
00:09:18.870 --> 00:09:22.531
That's about the population  of the entire nation of Canada,
这大概相当于加拿大 整个国家人口的数量，

150
00:09:22.531 --> 00:09:25.999
where we're sitting today.
这就是目前的状况。

151
00:09:25.999 --> 00:09:29.303
This is why, over time, I have come to call this epidemic of violence
这就是为什么， 我将这遍布的暴力称之为

152
00:09:29.303 --> 00:09:31.592
the Locust Effect.
